			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~Tony+Isaac">Tony Isaac</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~Tony+Isaac">( 1301187 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64193530">		
		on Saturday January 27, 2024 @09:51PM (<span class="ind"></span><a href="//news.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23207450&amp;cid=64193530">#64193530</a>)
		<small><a href="http://www.isaacsoft.com/" title="http://www.isaacsoft.com/" class="user_homepage_display">Homepage</a> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64193530"><p><div class="quote"><p>owning infinitely inflating dollars is looked on less favorably now than in the past</p></div><p>US inflation rate spiked in 2022, yes, but it has since come back down to a manageable 3.4%. That's lower than the average for the world (4.9%).</p><p><a href="https://www.euromonitor.com/article/global-inflation-tracker-q4-2023-inflation-eases-despite-high-economic-uncertainty#:~:text=Under%20the%20baseline%20scenario%2C%20global,down%20from%206.9%25%20in%202023" title="euromonitor.com">https://www.euromonitor.com/ar...</a> [euromonitor.com]</p><p>By contrast, BRIC nations averaged around 5% in 2023. <a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/741754/inflation-rate-in-the-bric-countries/#:~:text=Inflation%20rate%20in%20the%20BRICS%20countries%20from%202000%20to%202028" title="statista.com">https://www.statista.com/stati...</a> [statista.com], China's rate appears low, but economists do not believe China's reporting.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64193530">
