	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64193474"><p>China's economy isn't exactly flourishing these days. <a href="https://www.newsweek.com/china-youth-unemployment-economic-crisis-1864513" title="newsweek.com">https://www.newsweek.com/china...</a> [newsweek.com] China's currency may catch on with BRIC nations, but probably not Western ones, any time soon. China is gaining power, but a lot of that power has been built on pretense. It's going to take a lot to unseat the US dollar as the world's reserve currency.</p></div>
