	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64193568"><p>Not to mention China's birth rate is continuing to plummet and there is suspicion that they may be inflating reports of their population and birth rates, so they may be even lower than reported. On top of that, about 70% of Chinese household assets are real-estate with at least 65 million homes being unoccupied and not likely to be occupied anytime soon. That is a lot of a household's wealth in one basket. If China doesn't slow down on this new construction and the birth rate continues to decline, their entire economy will collapse and bankrupt pretty much every citizen. My guess is they've got maybe 10 years to "fix" at least one of those problems, and if they don't it will only take another 5-10 years for the collapse to happen. Manufacturers have already started looking for alternatives, and a couple I've read about have already moved out of China to places like Vietnam and India.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64193568">
